    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-04-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-04-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="431" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d431">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hirsch</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-04-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 20, 1891</hi>
                        </date>.
                            (Received May 5.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 432.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my No. 397 of February 29, 1892,
                        and No. 424 of April 3, 1892, in relation to detention of letters addressed
                        to Americans in this empire, I now have the honor of reporting that
                        instructions have gone from the Sublime Porte to all the post-office
                        officials not to permit any detentions of letters addressed to
                        Americans.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Solomon Hirsch.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
